I see the proposals (roughly three, so far) as being very similar.

Clearly, bribing an unsworn has to be significantly more difficult
than hiring him.  I see a lot of room to work here, though.

	maybe it already is
	bribing indeps can be more expensive
	it can have less of a chance of success
	it can be impossible (say, if they're working)
	it can have a much greater chance of success
	   if the noble has been working for you for a while

Let's come back to that.

If the faction tag on units is hidden, then there is a new dimension of
intrigue.  The owner of the unit gets the report of everything it sees
and does.  The noble who hired the unit, however, does not.  Perhaps that
sea-captain you hired is really in the employ of your sworn enemy?


autotrain <list>		Train men if possible.
autohonor <amount>		Honor self with the given amount of gold
				each month.  If amount is "all", the noble
				will spend all of its gold on itself.
				autohonor 0 turns off automatic honoring.
				autohonor work applies same amount PAYed each
				month to honor


