o Osswid the Constructor [501], with:
    The Townsmen, 14 peasants
    The Guard, 5 soldiers
  - Feasel the Wicked [502], with:
      Rowdies, 10 soldiers
  - Kosar [505], with:
      1 peasant

The idea here is that there is a name string associated with each type
of unit.  If a unit of that type exists and a name exists, it is
displayed.  In the above example, "The Townsmen", "The Guard", and
"Rowdies" are names set by the player.  The one peasant hasn't had a
name set yet.  This would allow for a little more personalization of
units with a minimum of coding.  I suspect that "a lack of
personality" will be one of the primary complaints you will get about
the men-as-inventory and this should -- at least cosmetically -- be a
reasonable response to such complaints.  You did say you wanted a
"role-playing" feel.  

